title: For Sale/Trade:  UTAS UTS-15 Upgraded Package
postcontent: NOTE: Manufacturer is not CZ USA, it is UTAS.  I have listed it as CZ USA because UTAS is not listed, and UTAS is a Turkish shotgun manufacturing company, like the one CZ uses to make their shotguns.Up for sale is my UTAS UTS-15. I got it as a Gen 1, barebones model. I have since sent it to UTAS to be retrofitted with all of the upgrades to make it a Gen 3, and now it cycles everything reliably. I've shot high brass, low brass, and no brass (estate hulls are all plastic), and they all cycle perfectly.Included with this sale:- Original Box- UTAS UTS-15 shotgun in like new condition- 7" UTAS barrel extension- Aluminum pop-up sights- ATI Scorpion AR-15 X2 Recoil Pistol Grip (shotgun accepts standard AR-15 grips.)- UTS-15 Laser/LED Flashlight internal unit (no longer made or available as far as I know)- Cheapo eBay rubber ladder rail coversI'm selling because although I love this shotgun, it's no longer my home defense gun (I need lefty-friendly HD guns now that my wife needs to be able to use them, so bullpups are a no-go), although it would be great for that purpose for most people. It is overall very short, comfortable, with a generous recoil pad on the stock, and soft rubber on the back of the grip as well. The integrated laser/light can be switched using the trigger finger very easily, and it's a quality light that runs on two CR123A batteries.I got the extended barrel so that I could practice with clays, but I never really used it, because I forgot it at home almost every time.In my experience, after the retrofit, this shotgun has been dead reliable, as a shotgun should be. Although there is another bullpup shotgun design out there the KSG, I would not compare the two. Having fired both, the UTS-15 is superior in every way, except maybe weight.The shotgun has been stored in a humidity controlled safe all its life.I'm asking $1000 for this package.Additional images Album: https://imgur.com/a/ziUN3Text is best: REDACTED
